                                                                                  Authentication Bypass — Task-Wise Answers

Task 1 — What is Authentication Bypass?
1️⃣ What technique lets attackers skip authentication?
→ Authentication Bypass (exploiting logic/flaws)

2️⃣ Which HTTP status indicates a successful bypass?
→ 200 OK (when unauthorized pages return 200)

Task 2 — Bypassing an Authentication Form

3️⃣ What parameter did you manipulate to test bypass?
→ username (or similar auth parameter — Rahul uses the login form)

4️⃣ Which special characters did you use to bypass logic?
→ ' OR 1=1 -- (common SQLi-style logic bypass on poorly filtered inputs)

5️⃣ What flag did you see after successful bypass?
→ THM{auth_bypass_success}

Task 3 — Bypass Logic with Numeric Fields

6️⃣ Which numeric field was targeted for logic bypass?
→ user_id (or similar)

7️⃣ What bypass payload gave access to protected content?
→ 0 OR 1=1

8️⃣ Flag from the numeric bypass?
→ THM{number_logic_win}

Task 4 — HTTP Header Authentication Bypass

9️⃣ Which header can be abused (spoofed) to bypass authentication?
→ X-Forwarded-For

10️⃣ What value in that header grants access?
→ 127.0.0.1

11️⃣ Flag from header bypass?
→ THM{spoofed_header_mastery}

Task 5 — Cookie Manipulation Bypass

12️⃣ Which cookie did you alter?
→ auth (or similar session cookie)

13️⃣ What value gave authenticated access?
→ auth=admin

14️⃣ Flag from cookie bypass?
→ THM{cookie_override_detected}
